uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model

Class CEditability

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.CEditability

  • public class CEditability
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the editability from the client perspective of the instantiations of a particular CSlot. Covers instance editability status, as represented via IEditability, for instances of the slot on both assertions and queries.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static CEditability DEFAULT
      Represents the default editability where, for normal slots, the slot has IEditability.CONCRETE_ONLY editability on assertions, and IEditability.FULL editability on queries (see ISlot.getEditability() for a discussion of the exceptional case of "disjuncts-slots").

      • getStrongest

        public CEditability getStrongest(CEditability other)
        Derives the "strongest" editability status between this and the other specified value. This will be a CEditability whose assertions-status and queries-status will each be the strongest for the two values (see IEditability.getAssertionsStrongest(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IEditability) and IEditability.getQueriesStrongest(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IEditability)).
        Parameters:
        other - Editability status to test against this one
        Returns:
        Strongest editability status
